reviews.text: Nice outlet in the shopping mall. Serve a combination menu with Asian and Western fusion. We were there for afternoon tea and ordered a nice Taiwanese/Western Pork burger on a Chinese bun with sweet potatoes and one Napoleon cake, with got coffee and ice bubble tea. Served promptly. Recommended.

Nice, good quality and value  Korean/ Taiwanese food.  Service is quick. Good for a quick bite to eat or coffee with a friend and you want some nibbles. Or take the family there for a cheapish dinner out if you don't want to cook.

Food was above average, nothing spectacular. The beef noodle was good, however the braised pork was really dry, a couple pieces tasted like pork jerky. Fun kids menu. Clean comfortable environment. result.name: Starbucks

reviews.text: I like this place, pretty designed, comfortable tables and chairs.good for chatting and computer usage.

A bigger Starbucks outlet in the mall. Nice seating area, good service and great coffee. They offer limited free WiFI. Be careful never go there after school are out. Full of students doing home work and sit on one drink for hours.
Good place for a quick lunch, coffee and a place to relax.

Not the best service. Twice within the last month, the sales person insist that I use their term venti, grande, etc. when I was ordering, even though I clearly told them I wanted a medium size hot latte and physically pointed to that cup. They still acted like I was speaking French, and keep asking me, insisting "you mean Grande? Or Venti". How ridiculous. Like they are better than the customer and that all customer must speak the Starbucks language. Oddly enough I've never had this happen at other Starbucks here in Hong Kong. Very disappointed and disrespected and will try to visit other Starbucks instead of this one. Or maybe skip Starbucks altogether. Horrible customer service and attitude.
Excellent place for relax and reading. The missing star is to the Starbucks' staff (the managess) who was not friendly, (for many times that I've paid visit)

今天點了炸雞排肉燥飯，炸豬排肉燥飯，花枝麻醬拌麵，蠔咯。蠔咯只有10隻蠔仔，一大堆脆醬，油得基本上不能入口，因連同魚露及辣醬上枱，點辣醬可去除少少油，才得以入口，其餘3款不過不失。服務員態度有待改善，無禮貌，豬排飯已吃完，蠔咯還未到，就追問，服務員黑口黑面地說“等3分鐘呀”又唔會話“唔好意思，幫你地追追”連這種基本服務態度也沒有。到櫃臺前埋單，3百幾元找數，多謝亦無一句，雖然3百幾元不是大數，但這是服務行業基本禮貌。
